## 3.  How to compile & link

Assuming the source files are placed as `pcapng.mli`, `pcapng.ml` (a tiny stub that only opens/closes/iterates) and `pcapng_stubs.c`:

```bash
# 1. generate the .cmo/.cmx for the tiny pure‑OCaml wrapper
ocamlc -c pcapng.mli
ocamlc -c pcapng.ml        # contains only external declarations

# 2. compile the C++ stub (need a C++ compiler)
ocamlc -c -ccopt -std=c++17 pcapng_stubs.c

# 3. build a library
ocamlc -a -o libpcapng.cma pcapng.cmo pcapng_stubs.o
ocamlopt -a -o libpcapng.cmxa pcapng.cmx pcapng_stubs.o
```

When linking a final program:

```bash
ocamlc -o my_prog unix.cma libpcapng.cma my_prog.ml -cclib -lstdc++
# or with native code:
ocamlopt -o my_prog unix.cmxa libpcapng.cmxa my_prog.ml -cclib -lstdc++
```

Make sure the directory that contains `pcapng.h` (the libpcapng header) is on the compiler’s include path (e.g. `-I/path/to/libpcapng/include`).

